Date Of Last Update: 26/02/2026

Key Tech:
Oracel Cloud, Putty

In this file contains:
A step by step tutorial on how to host a website for free using Oracle Cloud Free Tier virtual machine

Steps:

CREATING THE VM
1. In Menu select compute > instance then Create a new instance (free tier only allows 2)

2. In Creation set image to Ubuntu, and shape to VM.Standard.E2.1.Micro (we dont pick the more powerfull Ampere as free instance)

3. In Networking Tab during creation remember to download and save SSH keys

4. Create The VM

SETTING UP NETWORK
5. Access the VM and click on Networking, then click the Subnet, then click Security, then click the Secuirtyy List, then click Security Rules

6. On this page we want ot add a Ingress Rule Just to allow us access details are
Source Type: CIDR
Source CIDR: 0.0.0.0/0
IP Protocol: TCP
Destination Port Range: 80
Description (optional but reccomended) : Allow HTTP Connections 

CONNECTING FROM LOCAL MACHINE
1. Download Putty and PuttyGen
2. Launch Putty Gen and press load select your saved private key, then press save private key
3. Now on standard putty go to connection>ssh>Auth>Credentials and open your newly saved key
4. Copy username and the public IP address from Oracle into Putty Host Name  in format "username@publicip" then press open (dont worry about the port, name it whatever)

INSIDE THE SERVER TERMINAL
1. Do "sudo apt update" then "sudo apt upgrade"  just upgrades dependencies

